<div id="review_1777333063" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1777333063" />
    <a title="Lars Jerlach" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/60302447-lars-jerlach"><img alt="Lars Jerlach" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1490463190p2/60302447.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1777333063?book_show_action=true">Oct 06, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lars Jerlach" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lars Jerlach" href="/user/show/60302447-lars-jerlach">Lars Jerlach</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1777333063" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4679015184227738516">Forever is one of the best books I have read in a very long time. I closed the book with a feeling of regret knowing that I wouldn&apos;t read a story this good for quite some time. It&apos;s a beautifully written and haunting story that is deeply rooted in the heart of New York, but one that fundamentally speaks about the mysteries of human condition and the things we feel but cannot fully articulate. <br/>This remarkable hybrid is an absorbing, satisfying read and the story stays with you a long time after y</span>
  <span id="freeText4679015184227738516" style="display:none">Forever is one of the best books I have read in a very long time. I closed the book with a feeling of regret knowing that I wouldn't read a story this good for quite some time. It's a beautifully written and haunting story that is deeply rooted in the heart of New York, but one that fundamentally speaks about the mysteries of human condition and the things we feel but cannot fully articulate. <br />This remarkable hybrid is an absorbing, satisfying read and the story stays with you a long time after you close the book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4679015184227738516" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


